	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=/db/poster.html?user=225801><span id= >Lundaein</span></a><br><span id=notbold>235 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.57]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I don't mind having pets to add to my spell dps. I don't mind having a lower dps because my pet + my dps would be around the same as a class that has no pet's dps. What I DO mind is the fact that I HAVE to have a pet up to do any decent dps at all. Ever heard of a &quot;spawn on death&quot; mob, as some call them?<br><br>Some of them drop decent mage usable items, but as for usefulness on this type of raid for a mage (and even BSTs), it's very low. In addition, as mob levels go up, pets land less and less spells on them, and do less and less dps. This starts to taper off at a much lower level for the pet than it does the mage. A mage's dps is more constant going from mobs from levels, say, 64 to 66 at level 70 than a pet's is. Thus, if this were to increase a CoWind's dps by, say, 20%, the pure dps increase would get lower and lower as the mobs went up in level, while the mage's spell dps remained more constant. Thus, a 20% increase in the mage's dps might be better, considering whether or not the mage's spell dps is higher than his pets. I do not know, I'd have to look at parses, as I'm not level 70 yet.<br><br>Edit: One thing about pets having a high dps vs spells, I do have to say, is that one would have to spend less mana on spells to nuke to solo a mob and have pets at the same amount of health.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jan&nbsp;&nbsp;6 08:12:53 2005</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1015784" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1015784</a><br>I'm workin' on it!</td></tr>
